des:
Amazon Alexa makes it easier than ever to adjust your UBROAD lighting products.
You can simply ask Alexa to turn on, turn off or dimmer the light. 
There’s no need to go to the switch to adjust you home light - just talk to Alexa on your Amazon Echo, Echo Dot or Tap. 

After connecting Alexa to your UBROAD Smart products in a few simple steps:
(1). Register one UBROAD account in our "UBROAD" app;
(2). You need to have some UBROAD WiFi Dimmer devices in hand;
(3). Edit these devices in our "UBROAD" app and change appropriate name for your devices which will be used in "UBROAD" skills;
(4). In "UBROAD" app edit device advanced to open "M2M" function;
(5). Download Amazon "Alexa" app;
(6). Configure Echo with "Alexa" app;
(7). Search "UBROAD" skill from the "Alexa" app skills category;
(8). Click Enable skill of "UBROAD", and you'll be navigated to UBROAD login page;
(9). Input your UBROAD account email and password, you'll be redirect to the success page;
(10). Now all setup is finished. 

You can use the UBROAD skill to either turn the lights on/off by saying, for example: 
“Alexa,discover my devices.”
“Alexa,turn on the bedroom light.”
“Alexa,turn off the bedroom light.”

Or dim the lights to a desired setting: 
“Alexa,set the bedroom light to 50%.”
“Alexa,increase the bedroom light by 50%.”
“Alexa,decrease the bedroom light by 50%.”

Currently this skill supports products:
smart wifi dimmer
smart wifi switch

If you have any problem when you use this skill, you can contact us with email : service@ubroad-tek.com
